---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'BUPA Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Best Expat Insurance', href: '/best/expat-health-insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'BUPA Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', bupa: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', bupa: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Mental Health Parity', bupa: true, cigna: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', bupa: 'Included (Elite)', cigna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Dental', bupa: 'Included (Premier+)', cigna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Vision', bupa: 'Included (Premier+)', cigna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Telemedicine', bupa: '24/7 Global', cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', bupa: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Second Medical Opinion', bupa: 'Included', cigna: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'No-Claims Discount', bupa: true, cigna: false },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'BUPA Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 30', bupa: '$200-300/mo', cigna: '$140-180/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', bupa: '$350-450/mo', cigna: '$220-280/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 35', bupa: '$400-550/mo', cigna: '$280-360/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', bupa: '$700-950/mo', cigna: '$450-600/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="BUPA Global vs Cigna Global"
  description="Compare BUPA Global and Cigna Global international health insurance. See coverage, pricing, and which premium plan is right for you."
  headline="BUPA Global vs Cigna Global: Premium Expat Insurance Compared"
  subheadline="Two top-tier international health insurance providers. Here's how they stack up on coverage, price, and service."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    BUPA Global and Cigna Global are both premium international health insurance providers with strong reputations. If you're looking for comprehensive coverage and don't mind paying more for quality, these are two of the best options available.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">BUPA Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li><strong>Trustpilot:</strong> 4.4/5 stars</li>
        <li>Mental health covered equally to physical</li>
        <li>Pre-existing conditions often covered</li>
        <li>No shareholders (reinvests in healthcare)</li>
        <li>75+ years of healthcare experience</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Cigna Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li><strong>Network:</strong> 1.5M+ providers</li>
        <li>Strong family and maternity options</li>
        <li>24/7 multilingual customer service</li>
        <li>User-friendly online portal and app</li>
        <li>Generally lower premiums</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Providers"
    description="Get quotes from BUPA Global and Cigna Global for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    Both providers offer comprehensive coverage, but BUPA Global tends to include more benefits in their base plans while Cigna Global uses an add-on approach.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Key Differences</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> BUPA Global treats mental health equally to physical health with matching coverage limits. Cigna Global covers mental health but with more limitations.</li>
    <li><strong>Dental and vision:</strong> BUPA includes these in Premier and Elite plans. Cigna requires separate add-ons.</li>
    <li><strong>Second Medical Opinion:</strong> BUPA includes expert second opinions for complex conditions. Cigna offers more limited access.</li>
    <li><strong>No-claims discount:</strong> BUPA rewards claim-free years with premium discounts. Cigna doesn't offer this.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    BUPA Global is generally more expensive than Cigna Global, reflecting their more inclusive coverage approach. However, when you factor in BUPA's included benefits vs Cigna's add-ons, the gap may narrow.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices based on comprehensive plans excluding US coverage. Your actual quote may vary based on specific plan selection, deductible, and location.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Notes on Pricing</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>BUPA Global typically costs 30-50% more than Cigna Global</li>
    <li>BUPA's no-claims discount can reduce premiums over time</li>
    <li>Adding dental/vision to Cigna closes some of the price gap</li>
    <li>Both providers charge significantly more for US coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Actual Price"
    description="Estimates vary. See what you'd actually pay based on your details."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> has a larger network with over 1.5 million providers worldwide, giving you more options for direct billing.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>BUPA Global</strong> has a network of 1.7 million providers, slightly larger on paper, though direct billing availability varies by region.
  </p>
  <p>
    Both networks cover major hospitals and clinics in popular expat destinations. You're unlikely to have trouble finding care with either provider.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>BUPA Global</strong> has strong claims reviews, with customers praising timely settlements and few rejections. Their MembersWorld app handles claims digitally.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> also offers easy online claims and a well-designed app. Claims typically process within 5-10 business days.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    Both providers offer 24/7 multilingual support. BUPA Global includes access to in-house doctors and nurses. Cigna Global is known for responsive, helpful service.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Trustpilot comparison:</strong> BUPA Global (4.4/5) edges out most competitors on customer satisfaction ratings.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose BUPA Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Mental health coverage is a priority</li>
        <li>You have pre-existing conditions to consider</li>
        <li>You want dental/vision included (not add-ons)</li>
        <li>You value no-claims premium discounts</li>
        <li>You prefer a company focused on healthcare</li>
        <li>Budget is flexible for premium coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Cigna Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You want lower base premiums</li>
        <li>You prefer to add only the benefits you need</li>
        <li>You're a family needing maternity coverage</li>
        <li>Direct billing availability is important</li>
        <li>You value a user-friendly digital experience</li>
        <li>Cost-effectiveness matters more than extras</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Both BUPA Global and Cigna Global are excellent choices for expats who want comprehensive coverage. The right choice depends on your priorities and budget.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Choose BUPA Global</strong> if you want the most inclusive coverage, particularly for mental health, and don't mind paying a premium for it. Their approach to pre-existing conditions and no-claims discounts add extra value.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Choose Cigna Global</strong> if you want solid comprehensive coverage at a lower price point, with the flexibility to add only the extras you need. Their larger network and strong service reputation make them a safe choice.
  </p>
  <p>
    For most expats, Cigna Global offers the better value. But if mental health coverage, pre-existing condition handling, or all-inclusive benefits matter most, BUPA Global is worth the extra investment.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Compare quotes from both providers based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change frequently. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
